{"word":"G5217 - ὑπάγω - hypágō - hoop-ag'-o - Depart","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ὑπάγω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">hypágō</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">hoop-ag'-o</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Depart</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Verb / வினைச்சொல்</span>"},{"paragraph":"வினைச்சொல் - போ"},{"paragraph":"to lead under, bring under"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From <a href=\"#/G5259 - ὑπό - hypó - hoop-o'/5259\">G5259</a> and <a href=\"#/G71 - ἄγω - ágō - ag'-o/71\">G71</a>; to <i>lead</i> (oneself) <i>under</i>, that is, <i>withdraw</i> or <i>retire</i> (as if <i>sinking</i> out of sight), literally or figuratively: - depart, get hence, go (a-) way.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}